WEBVTT

00:00.194 --> 00:03.119
Oh, come on.

00:03.199 --> 00:04.101
I know it's summer.

00:04.121 --> 00:06.845
I know you've been at the beach all day, but you can do better than that.

00:06.885 --> 00:07.787
Are you feeling good?

00:07.847 --> 00:11.433
Turn to the person beside you and say, I'm feeling good.

00:11.493 --> 00:15.700
Turn to the other one and say, your summer tan looks gorgeous.

00:16.662 --> 00:19.346
If you're single, I'm trying to help you out.

00:19.714 --> 00:24.402
Listen, I am so excited to have the opportunity to share with you this weekend.

00:24.422 --> 00:25.965
I want to welcome all of our campuses.

00:26.205 --> 00:31.774
It's not just us here at Cooper City, but we have so many campuses right on the other side of that camera.

00:32.115 --> 00:32.776
We love you guys.

00:32.796 --> 00:34.359
Let's give it up for our campuses.

00:34.860 --> 00:36.082
We've got Halendale.

00:36.422 --> 00:37.865
We've got Pensacola.

00:38.225 --> 00:39.508
We have the Bahamas.

00:39.628 --> 00:43.314
We have Lima and Barranco, and we're so excited.

00:43.394 --> 00:50.923
that you guys have joined us at Potential Church at your location, and really believing that God is going to do some incredible things this weekend.

00:50.943 --> 00:54.668
We've been in this series called Subscribe for the Past Several Weeks.

00:55.389 --> 01:00.555
And we've really been talking about our ethos here at Potential Church.

01:00.575 --> 01:03.338
And ethos is just a fancy word that means values.

01:04.420 --> 01:09.586
And today I'm excited to have the opportunity to talk about the value of passion.

01:10.948 --> 01:13.010
And you know, if I can be honest with you,

01:13.314 --> 01:18.582
When I found out that I was going to be teaching on passion, I was actually really nervous.

01:18.642 --> 01:22.969
Now, I always get nervous before I prepare to speak in front of an audience.

01:22.989 --> 01:24.552
I think a little bit of nervous is a good thing.

01:24.612 --> 01:25.934
It keeps you on high alert.

01:25.954 --> 01:27.016
It keeps you on edge.

01:27.076 --> 01:28.598
It gives you a sticky mind.

01:28.618 --> 01:41.298
But I was particularly nervous about the topic of passion because I would say that passion is the number one thing that in 2017, the enemy has attempted to rob me of.

01:42.018 --> 01:43.960
And if I'm being really honest with you today, you know what?

01:44.000 --> 01:49.307
There are days, and there are even weeks at a time where the enemy has won that battle for my passion.

01:49.347 --> 01:52.691
My passion for God and my passion for His church.

01:53.732 --> 02:00.500
And so today, I don't come to preach at you or to condemn you, but to let you know we're all in this journey together.

02:01.762 --> 02:03.884
But I really believe in the value of passion.

02:03.924 --> 02:06.027
I believe in the power of passion.

02:06.047 --> 02:11.954
And so I just want to share with you some of the revelations that God has dropped in my heart this year.

02:12.418 --> 02:14.661
in recent months, even in recent weeks.

02:14.741 --> 02:20.850
And the one thing I love about our God is that He is a restore of all the things that the enemy takes from us.

02:21.611 --> 02:27.340
And even though the enemy may win some battles, we know that He's already lost the war according to the scripture.

02:27.420 --> 02:29.563
And for some of us, maybe that's it.

02:29.603 --> 02:31.686
We just lose a battle.

02:32.427 --> 02:39.858
And instead of moving forward and learning from that failure or that defeat or that mistake,

02:40.418 --> 02:43.901
We keep replaying the loss over and over again in our minds.

02:43.982 --> 02:52.470
And so we become tired because it feels as if though we've been fighting hundreds of battles when in reality, we've just been fighting the same one over and over and over again for years.

02:53.891 --> 02:59.217
And so today my prayer is that as we gather around the Word of God that He would speak to us.

02:59.677 --> 03:03.080
And I love the passage in Jeremiah chapter 17.

03:03.100 --> 03:07.204
If you got your Bibles, turn with me to Jeremiah chapter 17.

03:07.244 --> 03:08.786
We're gonna read a few verses.

03:08.930 --> 03:13.214
And you know, I'm gonna preach a little bit differently than normally.

03:13.254 --> 03:15.336
I don't have like point one, two, three.

03:15.377 --> 03:20.201
I really just wanna break down Jeremiah 17 verses five through eight.

03:21.102 --> 03:25.827
And can I tell you, I read it actually, it popped up on my Bible app.

03:25.867 --> 03:27.269
It was my verse for the day.

03:27.709 --> 03:29.871
And when I read it, God instantly spoke to me.

03:29.911 --> 03:31.853
And so I wanna share it with you.

03:31.873 --> 03:36.658
Jeremiah chapter 17, we're gonna start in verse five, and I'm actually gonna read from

03:37.538 --> 03:43.807
Not my iPad, but my physical Bible, because it makes me, it makes you more spiritual, right?

03:43.827 --> 03:49.195
You know, the headline for this passage of scripture is wisdom from the Lord.

03:50.817 --> 03:53.621
You know, I love that our God is the supplier of all wisdom.

03:54.322 --> 03:57.607
When we don't know what to do in our situation, our God knows exactly what to do.

03:57.647 --> 04:02.855
And the title, the title is wisdom from the Lord.

04:02.875 --> 04:05.138
It says this, it says, this is what the Lord says.

04:05.858 --> 04:14.453
Cursed are those who put their trust in mere humans, who rely on human strength and turn their hearts away from the Lord.

04:15.235 --> 04:19.182
They are like stunted shrubs in the desert with no hope for the future.

04:19.783 --> 04:24.291
They will live in the barren wilderness in an uninhabited, salty land.

04:25.754 --> 04:30.482
But in verse seven, it says, but blessed, but blessed, but blessed.

04:30.722 --> 04:35.489
are those who trust in the Lord and have made the Lord their hope and confidence.

04:35.529 --> 04:38.193
Why don't you underline or circle that word made?

04:39.976 --> 04:50.471
Those who trust in the Lord and have made the Lord their hope and confidence, they are like trees planted along a river bank with roots that reach deep into the water.

04:50.491 --> 04:54.878
Such trees are not bothered by the heat or worried by long months of drought.

04:55.859 --> 05:00.306
Their leaves stay green and they never stop

05:00.546 --> 05:02.128
Producing fruit.

05:03.450 --> 05:06.695
The title of my message today is simply this, stay green.

05:07.477 --> 05:08.498
Will you bow your heads with me?

05:09.299 --> 05:14.908
Father, I thank you so much for the opportunity to share my heart today, God.

05:16.911 --> 05:26.866
And Father, I know that there are those who are sitting here today at every one of our campuses, God, and they feel dead on the inside.

05:27.074 --> 05:38.326
that passion that they once had for that career or that startup business or that marriage or that friendship or that dream God, that that passion has dwindled away.

05:38.386 --> 05:43.151
But God, I believe today that you want to restore all that the enemy has taken.

05:43.211 --> 05:46.936
God, that you want to restore a double portion of what the enemy has taken.

05:46.976 --> 05:48.697
So Father, we commit this moment to you.

05:50.159 --> 05:56.626
Father, I pray that you would stir up a passion in us so that our leaves may stay green.

05:57.058 --> 06:01.203
in full of life all year long.

06:01.283 --> 06:04.267
And it's in Jesus' name that we pray.

06:04.327 --> 06:09.473
Come on, if you believe that's a name above all names, why don't you just give God a shot of praise in this place.

06:12.116 --> 06:12.437
Amen.

06:13.638 --> 06:13.778
Amen.

06:13.798 --> 06:20.306
You know, if you don't know me, and those of you who do would probably say, I tend to be a pretty passionate person.

06:20.834 --> 06:24.259
All right, I am passionate in almost everything that I do.

06:24.279 --> 06:27.444
You know, my brother and I taught, y'all were here, we taught a few weeks ago.

06:28.265 --> 06:31.550
Me and my younger brother, he's, I don't know, how old is he, 22?

06:31.670 --> 06:33.012
How old am I, 25?

06:33.172 --> 06:33.713
Yeah, he's 22.

06:34.634 --> 06:37.799
And we have completely opposite personalities.

06:38.200 --> 06:39.922
See, Carson, he's the chill one.

06:40.642 --> 06:41.523
He's chill.

06:41.543 --> 06:43.045
He's kind of the peacemaker.

06:43.525 --> 06:46.769
He's the nice brother, I like to say.

06:47.109 --> 06:52.615
When we were in school, he was always able to get out of stuff.

06:52.896 --> 06:54.578
He would turn in assignments late.

06:54.858 --> 06:56.179
He would forget to do his homework.

06:56.200 --> 06:57.521
He really wasn't the best student.

06:58.222 --> 07:02.527
But he would be able to get away with it, because all he had to do was give his smile to his teachers.

07:02.867 --> 07:04.949
He had this way of charming.

07:05.350 --> 07:09.074
Everybody around him, and listen, I'm sorry, but I do not have a charming personality.

07:09.570 --> 07:11.933
All right, but you're stuck with me this weekend.

07:12.333 --> 07:14.476
But we have complete different personalities.

07:14.636 --> 07:16.298
I have more of an intense personality.

07:16.959 --> 07:19.402
And my family actually likes to make fun of me for it.

07:19.442 --> 07:22.105
My wife, she actually makes fun of me when I'm on the phone.

07:22.886 --> 07:31.957
Because when I'm on the phone, when I'm talking to somebody, it is impossible for me to stay seated or to stay not moving.

07:32.037 --> 07:33.238
Anybody else any pacers?

07:33.579 --> 07:36.402
When you're on the phone, you just pace back and forth.

07:36.706 --> 07:37.768
All right, yeah, that's me.

07:38.208 --> 07:43.737
So there'll be, oftentimes, I'm at home and I'll take a phone call and I'll be speaking and I'll walk all around the house.

07:44.278 --> 07:45.139
I mean, I will do laps.

07:45.240 --> 07:46.141
I'll go upstairs.

07:46.201 --> 07:47.082
I'll come downstairs.

07:47.123 --> 07:48.004
I'll walk to the kitchen.

07:48.084 --> 07:49.326
I'll walk to the living room.

07:49.346 --> 07:51.710
I'll walk into every single bedroom.

07:51.730 --> 07:56.998
And then I'll walk back to my wife after the phone call and I have sweat dripping down my brow.

07:57.379 --> 07:59.442
And she's like, wow, the phone call went that bad.

08:00.578 --> 08:01.680
I'm just intense.

08:01.760 --> 08:02.762
You know, I can't stay seated.

08:02.782 --> 08:03.343
I'm passionate.

08:03.383 --> 08:05.587
I talk on the phone like, you know, with my hands.

08:06.048 --> 08:06.609
Anybody else?

08:06.709 --> 08:07.911
Any Latins out there?

08:08.372 --> 08:10.115
Even when you're on the phone and nobody can see you.

08:10.135 --> 08:11.177
You're talking with your hands.

08:12.319 --> 08:21.495
And, you know, at times I've even been guilty, as I'm sure we all have, of letting my anger get the best of me and calling it passion.

08:22.998 --> 08:25.362
You know, back many months ago, we, um,

08:25.890 --> 08:35.025
We had service, it was a Saturday night, and we, the team missed a queue, an important queue in service, and I really wasn't pleased with the way the service had turned out.

08:35.085 --> 08:42.898
So we did debrief afterwards, and I gathered everybody together, and we're figuring out what's going on, and I'm firm, but I'm calm.

08:43.362 --> 08:45.885
All right, we've got to change this up for tomorrow.

08:45.906 --> 08:46.927
This isn't acceptable.

08:46.987 --> 08:47.768
What happened?

08:47.788 --> 08:48.870
What can we improve on?

08:48.910 --> 08:49.851
What can we learn from this?

08:50.211 --> 08:54.758
And someone, I won't mention your names, but said something that just ticked me off.

08:54.778 --> 08:55.799
You know what I'm talking about?

08:56.080 --> 08:58.783
When you are trying so hard to hold on to your salvation.

08:59.204 --> 09:06.654
And remember that you are saved and redeemed by the blood of Jesus, but then somebody says something so stupid.

09:07.035 --> 09:09.458
And you're like, all right, Holy Spirit, all bets are off.

09:10.658 --> 09:11.880
Yeah, that was me in that moment.

09:11.920 --> 09:13.823
I started to talk a little bit louder.

09:14.604 --> 09:16.287
Started to get a little bit more passionate.

09:17.148 --> 09:20.894
And the team just kind of looks back at me while I go off on about a five-minute rant.

09:20.914 --> 09:22.055
And at the very end, this is what I said.

09:22.075 --> 09:24.058
I said, guys, I'm not angry.

09:24.740 --> 09:25.641
I'm just passionate.

09:26.683 --> 09:28.325
They still make fun of me to this day.

09:28.365 --> 09:30.168
And actually, oh, man, you know what?

09:30.188 --> 09:30.689
I forgot it.

09:30.749 --> 09:35.997
If anybody's backstage, can you bring out the thing that I'm going to show to the congregation?

09:36.017 --> 09:36.778
I can't believe I forgot it.

09:36.798 --> 09:39.442
But I want to show you my most

09:39.746 --> 09:42.670
Recent product of my passion.

09:42.690 --> 10:01.899
I think my wife is running back there to get it now So we'll give us a few minutes, but I'm gonna show you it's actually my phone All right is the recent product of my passion and when you see this phone you'll see exactly why see it was Last week I got some troubling news and so I went to my wife We were alone.

10:01.919 --> 10:04.242
It was just the two of us and I was talking to her about it and and

10:04.322 --> 10:08.829
And I was sharing and, you know, we kind of got into a little bit of an argument.

10:08.869 --> 10:09.951
She felt one way about it.

10:10.051 --> 10:10.953
I felt a different way.

10:10.973 --> 10:14.138
And then so she left the room.

10:14.158 --> 10:14.899
Thank you so much.

10:15.380 --> 10:16.321
She left the room.

10:17.263 --> 10:23.693
And when she did, I kind of just chucked my phone and it slid across the table and hit a cabinet.

10:24.294 --> 10:26.137
And this is what ended up happening.

10:26.498 --> 10:29.983
Can we get a close up shot of that so that everybody can see?

10:30.384 --> 10:31.826
Now I do have to confess,

10:31.938 --> 10:37.928
Some of you have asked what happened and I gave you the Christian answer and said I dropped it while I was praying with someone.

10:38.709 --> 10:39.911
But that's not the truth.

10:40.051 --> 10:40.532
I lied.

10:40.552 --> 10:43.757
I threw my phone and now I am paying the price.

10:43.777 --> 10:49.166
And when my wife walked back into the room and she saw my phone, I said, babe, I wasn't angry.

10:50.468 --> 10:51.730
I was passionate.

10:53.442 --> 10:59.250
Now I'm sure Pastor Troy would never do anything like that, but you got stuck with me this weekend.

10:59.290 --> 10:59.891
But you know what?

11:00.352 --> 11:16.454
I truly am a strong believer in passion, real passion, true passion, not misplaced anger, but true passion that burns on the inside of us, whether it's for a specific cause or a specific dream that God's called us to.

11:16.855 --> 11:21.842
I'm a believer that passion can take us places that our gift and our ability cannot

11:22.018 --> 11:24.321
Because passion is contagious.

11:24.902 --> 11:27.005
Passion is what stirs hearts.

11:27.085 --> 11:31.211
Passion is what awakens the heart of the world.

11:31.251 --> 11:37.740
And I believe it's impossible to live the life that God has called us to without passion.

11:37.760 --> 11:40.063
You know, at potential church, it's one of our values.

11:40.144 --> 11:44.289
And I put it there in the outline you received when you walked in, the definition.

11:44.329 --> 11:45.932
This is how we define passion.

11:45.952 --> 11:48.135
Now, it's actually a much longer definition.

11:48.175 --> 11:50.418
I took the very last sentence.

11:50.946 --> 11:56.656
Passion is an energetic and unyielding pursuit of the mission.

11:56.676 --> 11:58.278
And you know, I love that word pursuit.

11:59.420 --> 12:10.138
See, pursuit suggests that possessing passion, maybe for somebody in the house, restoring the passion that she once had requires a strategy.

12:10.198 --> 12:12.562
Passion has a strategy.

12:14.285 --> 12:14.866
And you know,

12:15.458 --> 12:25.172
If I can be honest once again with you, you know, I mentioned at the beginning my message that this has been kind of a journey that I've walked through this year in fighting to hold on to my passion.

12:25.212 --> 12:29.839
And in recent weeks, it was actually a Saturday and it was before service.

12:29.879 --> 12:32.863
And something in my heart just didn't feel right.

12:33.003 --> 12:34.325
I felt discouraged.

12:34.365 --> 12:35.467
I felt frustrated.

12:36.068 --> 12:37.049
I felt lonely.

12:37.109 --> 12:40.274
I felt like there was no one that I could speak to or talk to.

12:40.450 --> 12:42.897
And so I was trying to stay busy.

12:42.937 --> 12:46.426
How many of you, you're like, when something's going on, you just need to stay busy.

12:46.787 --> 12:52.242
Because the minute that you stop to think about things, it's like you're just gonna have an emotional breakdown, right?

12:52.503 --> 12:53.746
That was me.

12:53.858 --> 13:15.781
on that particular Saturday, and so I'm trying to stay busy, and I'm trying to just, you know, God is good, I know that God is good, and even though I'm frustrated, and even, you know, some things are going on personally in my life, I believe that God is good, I can get through this, and so I'm trying to stay busy, and I ended up walking upstairs, and when I did, I ran into my friend, he's actually on staff here at the church, some of you may know him, Danny Trippy.

13:17.102 --> 13:20.946
I ran into him, and if you know Danny, he is,

13:21.154 --> 13:23.637
the definition of passion and encouragement.

13:24.118 --> 13:27.863
And I ran into him and he asked me how I was doing and I gave the typical answer, oh, I'm great.

13:28.764 --> 13:28.905
Right?

13:28.925 --> 13:34.052
Because sometimes we can get really good at giving people the responses we think they want to hear.

13:34.773 --> 13:35.333
I'm great.

13:35.934 --> 13:36.875
Everything's fine.

13:36.895 --> 13:41.682
And he came and he got in my face and he said, no, Tyler, how are you really?

13:42.626 --> 13:47.232
And I think he could tell in my face, my eyes just began to, to welter up with tears.

13:47.312 --> 13:51.817
And he took a moment to stop to encourage me to speak life over me, to pray for me.

13:52.278 --> 13:56.323
And after he did that, can I tell you, I couldn't continue on being busy.

13:56.383 --> 13:59.507
I, I went to my office and I just began to have a moment with God.

13:59.527 --> 14:07.196
I, I began to cry and, you know, sometimes we dull our passion by trying to avoid our emotions.

14:08.618 --> 14:11.762
Some of us, we spend years staying busy.

14:12.418 --> 14:17.345
Moving on to the next task, just trying to get through the day, avoiding our emotions.

14:17.385 --> 14:21.350
And what that does is it dulls the passion that is on the inside of us.

14:21.410 --> 14:37.813
And my prayer today is that same moment I had on that Saturday that you would have that moment right here right now, that this would be a moment where you can pause, where you can eliminate the distractions from your mind and have a pause of true reflection.

14:38.654 --> 14:41.458
Because I believe that God wants to stir up your passion again today.

14:42.370 --> 14:46.855
And you know, I love Jeremiah 17, verse five, that very first verse.

14:47.676 --> 14:52.361
When it says, cursed are those who put their trust in mere humans and rely on human strength.

14:52.381 --> 14:58.908
And then the very next sentence says, and turn their hearts away from the Lord.

14:58.928 --> 15:04.314
See, I think scripture points out something very specific in this passage.

15:04.334 --> 15:10.080
It says that, cursed are those who rely on human strength.

15:10.601 --> 15:11.762
And then the very next

15:12.290 --> 15:15.454
portion of that sentence is and turn their hearts away from God.

15:15.474 --> 15:24.406
So it leads me to believe that there is a correlation between relying on our own strength and turning our hearts away from God.

15:25.507 --> 15:29.432
See, I don't know about you, but it's when I put my trust in my own strength that I get tired.

15:30.894 --> 15:31.075
Right?

15:31.115 --> 15:38.805
I get tired when I try and manufacture that dream or that vision or that project in my own timing.

15:38.825 --> 15:39.826
I get tired.

15:40.258 --> 15:50.472
When I am fighting the same battles over and over and over again, I get tired when I try and come up with the solution to every single problem.

15:50.492 --> 15:51.273
We get tired.

15:52.454 --> 15:57.501
We get tired when we rely on our strength rather than the strength of Almighty God.

15:59.123 --> 16:01.606
I get tired when I try and take the problem into my own hands.

16:02.828 --> 16:07.474
I get tired when sometimes I don't like God's response to the problem.

16:08.290 --> 16:11.455
And I think that I know better and I try and work it out.

16:12.817 --> 16:17.463
And it's not that we want to turn our hearts away from God.

16:18.465 --> 16:24.694
It's just that it's all so tempting to control the outcome of a situation.

16:26.376 --> 16:33.306
But see, that's why we're able to come to church and we're able to worship and lift our hands and we're able to smile.

16:33.327 --> 16:35.730
And when people ask us how we're doing, oh, I am blessed.

16:36.002 --> 16:48.635
I am blessed, God is so good, and we may be even reading our Bible every single day, but we can still have a heart that is turned away from God, because rather than relying on His strength, we're relying on our own.

16:50.777 --> 16:54.021
And it happens to every single one of us.

16:56.243 --> 16:58.465
And you know, it's not that we lose sight of the mission.

16:58.825 --> 17:03.250
We just lose the energy that is required to live in pursuit of the mission.

17:04.002 --> 17:05.784
I wrote it there in your outline like this.

17:06.946 --> 17:16.338
We rarely lose sight of the object of our passion, but rather we lose the energy required to live in pursuit of our passion.

17:17.159 --> 17:18.761
We just get tired of fighting the battles.

17:20.844 --> 17:28.153
And how many of you know sometimes it seems like just when you made it through one battle, barely making it out alive, the next battle is right around the corner?

17:29.094 --> 17:32.018
Can I tell you, when I've walked through those seasons where I have

17:32.418 --> 17:38.726
Seriously wondered if God has called me to ministry because I would come to church and I just didn't feel passionate.

17:39.207 --> 17:40.749
I didn't feel like praying with people.

17:40.989 --> 17:42.431
I needed somebody to pray with me.

17:42.771 --> 17:44.794
Can I tell you, wasn't that I didn't care about people?

17:45.094 --> 17:46.676
It wasn't that I lost sight of the mission.

17:46.716 --> 17:49.140
No, the mission is very clear at potential church.

17:49.180 --> 17:54.506
It is to partner with people to reach their God potential so that together we can impact our world for good.

17:54.526 --> 17:56.509
I never lost sight of the mission.

17:56.529 --> 18:00.434
I just lost the energy required.

18:01.218 --> 18:04.042
to go from battle to battle to battle to battle.

18:04.062 --> 18:07.166
Sometimes it just seems like the distance between the battles is too short.

18:09.049 --> 18:15.458
And we get tired because we rely on our strength and our wisdom rather than the strength of our God.

18:16.439 --> 18:18.682
But you know, I love what verse seven says.

18:19.643 --> 18:27.054
It says, but blessed is the man who trusts in the Lord and has made the Lord his hope and confidence.

18:27.715 --> 18:30.258
God will be in your life what you make of him.

18:31.810 --> 18:36.075
You know, back many years ago, when I was in youth ministry, I was in middle school at the time.

18:36.896 --> 18:37.897
I think seventh grade.

18:38.457 --> 18:42.322
And we had an event that we were doing in the youth ministry.

18:42.802 --> 18:44.264
And it was called maze craze.

18:45.205 --> 18:45.545
All right?

18:45.585 --> 19:00.882
And what this event was, and I will say we've come up with, I think, much more creative ideas these days in our youth ministry, but what this event was is there were cardboard boxes that were connected to make a maze.

19:01.442 --> 19:06.048
And the goal was, you know, you would come in and you would get down on your knees.

19:06.088 --> 19:07.590
You would crawl into the first box.

19:08.411 --> 19:10.654
And then this box would be a maze.

19:11.014 --> 19:13.518
You would have to try and figure your way out your way out.

19:14.159 --> 19:15.841
The last box was on the other side of the room.

19:16.682 --> 19:22.930
Now, I don't know if you spent much time in cardboard boxes lately, but they tend to be dark and small.

19:23.874 --> 19:27.057
And, you know, I have a little bit of claustrophobia.

19:27.077 --> 19:30.701
Anybody else, claustrophobia, it's a real, and I get it from my mom.

19:30.721 --> 19:34.124
I could tell you some really funny stories about that, but that's for a different sermon.

19:34.945 --> 19:37.187
So I was a little bit nervous, but you know, I'm not gonna be the kid.

19:37.207 --> 19:40.431
That's like, oh no, I don't wanna do it, you know, and get laughed at.

19:40.451 --> 19:50.461
So I get on all my knees and I crawl into this cardboard box, and to be honest with you, I had my eyes closed for about the first minute and a half, as I'm just moving through.

19:50.481 --> 19:51.602
I'm like, okay, if I can't,

19:52.226 --> 19:55.470
If I can't see how enclosed I am, then I'm not going to freak out.

19:56.131 --> 19:59.476
And everything's good until all of a sudden I hit the person in front of me.

19:59.896 --> 20:08.527
And when I open my eyes, I am in this small little tunnel and it is filled with kids as far as my eye can see.

20:08.808 --> 20:11.591
And all of a sudden I start to feel some panic rise up in me.

20:11.912 --> 20:13.314
I'm like, I'm never going to get out of this box.

20:13.934 --> 20:14.675
You know, that's how you feel.

20:14.695 --> 20:16.658
I'm like, I'm never getting out of this cardboard box.

20:16.802 --> 20:19.645
And there were little corners and I would like put my mouth up to it.

20:21.126 --> 20:23.769
Trying to suck in the air from the outside world.

20:23.829 --> 20:24.930
I felt trapped.

20:24.970 --> 20:29.395
And these kids weren't really, we were trying to figure our way out of the maze.

20:29.435 --> 20:31.196
So nobody was really moving very quickly.

20:32.378 --> 20:36.902
And it started getting loud and I could hear the chatter and all of a sudden I start sweating.

20:37.182 --> 20:39.465
And now by this time I am freaking out.

20:39.745 --> 20:44.850
And so what I did is I literally found one of the little

20:45.410 --> 20:52.900
openings that have been taped shut and I busted through the top of the maze and I climbed out and I was like, oh, I'm done with that.

20:52.940 --> 20:54.402
I'm not doing that again.

20:55.484 --> 20:59.148
But can I tell you some of us we do that in our relationship with God?

20:59.169 --> 21:09.202
We put him in a box and see if all God ever is to us is this supreme being who is mysterious and unrelatable and impersonal.

21:09.858 --> 21:12.817
then that's all he'll ever be in our lives.

21:12.877 --> 21:15.634
God will be what you make of him in your life.

21:17.090 --> 21:20.234
It's all about the lens and perspective through which we see God.

21:20.254 --> 21:42.899
But can I tell you, when you make God your joy, when you make God your strength, when you make God your peace, when you make Him your defender, when you make Him your vindicator, when you make Him your portion, when you make Him your hope, your confidence, your refuge in times of trouble, that is exactly who He will become in your life.

21:44.360 --> 21:45.842
God will be who we make Him to be.

21:46.690 --> 21:47.352
You say, you know what?

21:47.372 --> 21:48.715
I'm confused.

21:50.359 --> 21:52.745
I don't know what to do in my situation.

21:52.805 --> 21:54.369
I don't know what path to take.

21:54.990 --> 21:58.679
God says in Proverbs 3 that I will direct your steps.

21:59.401 --> 21:59.983
You say, you know what?

22:00.043 --> 22:01.426
I feel all alone today.

22:01.698 --> 22:05.464
I feel like there is not one person in my life that I can trust.

22:05.564 --> 22:07.568
I feel like everyone is out to get me.

22:07.588 --> 22:11.013
And every time I let someone in, they end up hurting me.

22:11.033 --> 22:19.887
God says in Deuteronomy 31, that I will never leave you, that I will never abandon you, but I will be with you everywhere you go.

22:19.988 --> 22:22.872
Even when you lock alone, I will be there with you.

22:22.912 --> 22:24.655
You say, you know what?

22:25.216 --> 22:28.882
I'm afraid to take that next step into the unknown.

22:29.826 --> 22:35.118
And I can't sleep at night because I am so consumed by fear and anxiety.

22:35.158 --> 22:42.514
God tells us in 2 Timothy that he has not given us a spirit of fear, but he's given us a spirit of power.

22:42.850 --> 22:49.520
when we feel like we can't face not one more battle that everything on the inside is dead.

22:49.580 --> 22:50.762
We have no passion.

22:51.022 --> 22:53.045
We have no more expectation.

22:53.385 --> 23:04.061
God tells us in 2 Corinthians, no, my grace is sufficient for you that you can boast in your weakness because the power of Christ rests on you.

23:04.101 --> 23:07.366
You may be in a season of unrest with the power of Christ.

23:07.827 --> 23:09.269
Rest on you.

23:09.309 --> 23:10.130
God will be.

23:10.658 --> 23:13.221
exactly what you need, when you need Him to be it.

23:14.662 --> 23:15.724
But who is God to you?

23:15.744 --> 23:16.905
What have you made Him in your life?

23:17.345 --> 23:18.507
Have you made Him a priority?

23:20.269 --> 23:21.550
Have you made Him your peace?

23:22.091 --> 23:23.592
Have you made Him your strength?

23:24.173 --> 23:27.316
Are you still trying to make it all happen in your own time?

23:27.336 --> 23:32.101
And can I tell you, when we rely on our own strength, that will dull our passion so quickly?

23:34.164 --> 23:38.849
Because we lose the strength that we need to move from battle to battle.

23:38.869 --> 23:39.890
And can I tell you?

23:40.514 --> 23:53.549
that in this season of my life, I've had to learn to make God my strength for the passion that I know is deep down, but just can't seem to make its way towards the surface.

23:53.569 --> 23:56.212
You know, sometimes passion doesn't look like we think it does.

23:57.013 --> 24:01.498
Sometimes it's not always this extroverted outward expression.

24:01.998 --> 24:05.342
Can I tell you, sometimes passion looks like showing up.

24:06.604 --> 24:08.626
It just looks like continuing to show up

24:09.954 --> 24:14.380
And I remember when I was wrestling, God just whispered this in my ear.

24:14.420 --> 24:15.261
He said, you know what, Tyler?

24:15.281 --> 24:19.086
There are gonna be seasons where you do not see the fruits of your labor.

24:19.827 --> 24:20.788
You're gonna work hard.

24:21.189 --> 24:22.350
You're gonna work day and night.

24:22.731 --> 24:28.518
You're gonna face some battles, but you will not see the fruit of your labor, but you will always see the fruit of your character.

24:29.359 --> 24:33.044
See, your character and your integrity, that's what showing up is.

24:33.084 --> 24:37.650
It's showing up to that job that you just no longer feel passionate about.

24:38.850 --> 24:40.333
You're just there for the paycheck.

24:40.353 --> 24:41.795
Oh, you once were passionate.

24:42.377 --> 24:48.388
You thought you were going to help people, but somewhere along the way, the enemy has dulled that passion.

24:48.408 --> 24:53.357
It's continuing to show up and not showing up lazily, but putting your best effort forward.

24:54.359 --> 24:56.082
Sometimes it's showing up in your marriage.

24:56.122 --> 24:56.983
It's being present.

24:57.024 --> 24:58.146
It's being engaged.

24:58.747 --> 25:00.530
It's not having all the right answers.

25:01.090 --> 25:03.033
It's not getting everything right all the time.

25:03.093 --> 25:05.476
Sometimes passion is simply just continuing to show up.

25:05.496 --> 25:06.637
And can I tell you what I have learned?

25:06.898 --> 25:10.923
If we continue to show up, even when we don't feel like it, eventually God will show out.

25:11.363 --> 25:12.565
And he will bless that career.

25:12.605 --> 25:13.806
He will bless that marriage.

25:13.826 --> 25:15.489
He will bless that dream.

25:15.889 --> 25:21.657
But we gotta keep showing up.

25:21.677 --> 25:23.739
So who is God to you?

25:26.022 --> 25:27.444
What have you made him in your life?

25:27.524 --> 25:28.946
Are you connected?

25:30.114 --> 25:30.975
to the source.

25:32.798 --> 25:42.212
You see, it's important that we stay connected to the source as we see in the next verse in Jeremiah 17, the first part of verse 8.

25:42.232 --> 25:53.288
It says that he who makes the Lord their hope and confidence says he is like a tree planted along a river bank with its roots reaching deep into the water.

25:54.169 --> 25:57.714
A tree not bothered by the heat nor worried.

25:57.890 --> 25:59.793
by long months of droughts.

25:59.813 --> 26:02.577
See, I love the picture that Jeremiah paints in this scripture.

26:04.440 --> 26:13.653
He compares someone who makes the Lord their hope and their confidence to a tree that is planted along a riverbank.

26:13.673 --> 26:18.801
And see, when that tree is planted along the riverbank, there may be no rain for months.

26:20.704 --> 26:27.634
There may be scorching heat, but the tree doesn't get destroyed because it's connected

26:27.970 --> 26:28.751
to the source.

26:29.592 --> 26:33.977
It's along the riverbank where its roots reach deep into the water.

26:33.997 --> 26:38.542
So it has a constant source that never one runs dry.

26:39.142 --> 26:53.137
And you see, when we make God our strength, when we allow Him to supply the energy that we need to live in pursuit of our passion, when we make Him our source, when we remain connected to the source.

26:53.157 --> 26:55.600
And listen, I'm not talking about pretend Christianity.

26:56.241 --> 26:57.362
I'm not talking about

26:58.562 --> 27:00.626
coming to church when it serves you best.

27:00.646 --> 27:08.579
I'm not talking about serving God when it's convenient for you, but I'm talking about being connected to the source.

27:08.599 --> 27:10.863
When we are connected to the source, then you know what?

27:10.963 --> 27:18.396
Even when we don't see the blessing come to pass, we can still live in pursuit of our passion because it's not the blessing that's our source.

27:19.317 --> 27:23.404
It's the giver of the blessing who is our source.

27:23.424 --> 27:24.466
You know, Pastor Matt,

27:24.578 --> 27:35.893
Said so brilliantly last weekend when he spoke on loyalty that sometimes loyalty will cost you more than it blesses you and can I tell you that sometimes staying connected to God will cost you more than it blesses you in the moment?

27:37.255 --> 27:54.258
But can I tell you when we remain faithful when we keep showing up when we rely on God to be our strength to get us through those Those moments where it feels like everything on the inside of us is dead when we don't quit when we don't give up Can I tell you we're just like that tree that's planted along the riverbank?

27:54.498 --> 28:03.082
And we may see no blessing poured down upon us in that moment, but we can rest assured that our God is working behind the scenes in the supernatural.

28:03.363 --> 28:10.002
We may see nothing taking place in the natural, but when we continue to show up

28:10.178 --> 28:31.767
to that job, when we continue to be present and engaged in that marriage, even though it's lost all of its spark, when we continue to chase after that dream, because of the conviction that God has placed in our hearts, we can rest assured that God's working in the supernatural, and God in the supernatural is not confined by limitations here on earth.

28:31.807 --> 28:34.891
He's not confined by time or capacity.

28:36.313 --> 28:37.394
And there is nothing.

28:37.858 --> 28:42.446
stopping him from intervening in that situation, and reigniting that passion.

28:43.167 --> 28:45.772
And there's nothing stopping you from moving forward.

28:48.456 --> 29:01.298
And when that happens, we can do exactly what the second part of verse eight says, says that the tree that's planted along the riverbank, because it's connected to a source, it's leaves stay green.

29:01.410 --> 29:16.887
and it goes right on producing all its luscious fruit, even though the heat is scorching, even though there's a drought, the tree that's planted along the riverbank goes right on producing all of its luscious fruit.

29:18.849 --> 29:27.138
You know, in the midst of frustration and challenge and fatigue, all the things that kill our passion, you and I are called and equipped to keep going and to keep producing.

29:29.280 --> 29:31.282
That's what being connected to the source will do.

29:32.162 --> 29:35.368
We're not dependent on the blessing, we're dependent on the blesser.

29:36.771 --> 29:39.797
You can keep going and you can keep producing fruit.

29:39.857 --> 29:48.114
See, we're called and we're equipped to be people that not only produce fruit in easy seasons, but we're called to produce fruit in every season.

29:48.290 --> 29:53.336
When the rest of the world is not producing fruit, we are called and positioned and equipped to produce fruit.

29:53.597 --> 29:58.403
When the rest of the world runs from the problem, we are called to run to the problem.

29:58.423 --> 30:08.135
When the rest of the world is abandoning, we are called to remain steadfast and loyal to keep going and to keep producing.

30:13.842 --> 30:17.266
You know, I don't know what the enemy has stolen from you.

30:19.490 --> 30:23.654
I don't know what's killed your passion.

30:23.674 --> 30:25.236
I can speak from my experience.

30:26.197 --> 30:28.639
It's at the distance between the battles seem too short.

30:32.223 --> 30:33.284
And maybe that's you today.

30:33.344 --> 30:40.211
You just feel like once you face one battle and once you conquer that one battle, it takes everything in you.

30:41.413 --> 30:46.738
And here's the next battle and the one after that and the one after that and the one after that.

30:49.090 --> 30:58.022
But can I just suggest to us today that maybe today is the day that we stop feeding our battle and start feeding the power of our God.

30:58.042 --> 31:02.688
You know, there's a story in Joshua chapter six, and this is where I'm going to end us today.

31:03.870 --> 31:09.036
Joshua chapter six, the people of Israel, God's chosen people.

31:10.138 --> 31:13.202
Joshua was called to lead them into the promised land.

31:14.914 --> 31:20.363
But see, the only problem with this land that God said that he had already delivered to them, it had their name on it.

31:20.383 --> 31:24.730
The problem was that there was a big wall surrounding the city as the wall of Jericho.

31:27.795 --> 31:39.474
See, God had already said, this is the land I am giving to you, but the problem is, is there were people living in that land, that there was a wall standing between the Israelites and the promise of God.

31:41.506 --> 31:44.770
And so God instructed Joshua, he said, listen, this is what I want you to do.

31:45.891 --> 31:50.256
I want you to rally up the priests and give them the ram's horns.

31:50.316 --> 32:00.467
And all of the Israelites, you are going to walk around that wall once a day for six days, blowing those ram's horns.

32:01.748 --> 32:04.651
And he says, I don't want you to shout.

32:06.273 --> 32:07.815
I don't want you to get too hype.

32:07.835 --> 32:10.898
I don't want you to do any of that.

32:11.234 --> 32:12.816
To remain still, remain quiet.

32:13.357 --> 32:16.682
Joshua actually told the people he's like, listen, when we do this thing, shut up.

32:17.003 --> 32:18.064
Don't even say a word.

32:19.186 --> 32:22.571
Because I don't want somebody talking us out of our blessing.

32:23.833 --> 32:30.022
And then they were instructed that on the seventh day, they were to walk around that wall of Jericho seven times.

32:30.402 --> 32:37.273
And on that seventh time, on the completion of that seventh lap, the Rams horns were to sound.

32:37.913 --> 32:40.978
And the people of Israel were instructed to shout.

32:41.154 --> 32:43.116
with everything they add in them.

32:43.176 --> 32:45.238
And God said that wall will come down.

32:46.440 --> 32:48.021
And you'll be able to go in and take the city.

32:48.041 --> 32:55.189
And so Joshua instructed the people of Israel and for six days, once a day, they made that lap around Jericho.

32:57.111 --> 33:03.818
And can I tell you, you know, when I look at Scripture, I'm always like reading between the lines and I'm thinking, these are people just like you and me.

33:03.838 --> 33:11.026
I mean, imagine if all of us here in this room, different personalities, different backgrounds, maybe some different belief systems,

33:11.810 --> 33:15.994
were to spend every day in close unison together, walking around a wall.

33:16.014 --> 33:18.316
I mean, I just think about some of the things that must have happened.

33:18.336 --> 33:25.023
You have to know that they got tired, that they got fatigued, they were hot, they were sweaty, they were smelly.

33:25.083 --> 33:33.591
There was probably that young couple somewhere in the middle, and they're walking, holding hands, saying they love one another.

33:34.972 --> 33:40.818
But then there's that family right behind them with the screaming and crying kids, ruining the moments.

33:41.154 --> 33:49.264
You gotta know that the person who was probably in charge of bringing the snacks, one of those days he didn't quite pack enough.

33:49.284 --> 33:50.986
People are hangry, you know what hangry is?

33:53.189 --> 34:00.038
You had to know that there was that one girl who saw her boyfriend marching a little too closely to that girl who had been flirting with him.

34:02.140 --> 34:04.323
I'm sure there were some disagreements that broke out.

34:05.484 --> 34:09.970
But the word tells us that when the time came on that seventh lap,

34:10.114 --> 34:16.081
when they stood there and those horns sounded that the Israelites lifted up a battle cry.

34:16.321 --> 34:20.405
They lifted up a shout with everything that was inside of them.

34:20.425 --> 34:22.027
And it wasn't a shout of defeat.

34:22.347 --> 34:24.570
It wasn't a shout of tiredness.

34:24.650 --> 34:28.835
It wasn't a shout of fear.

34:28.915 --> 34:30.957
It was a shout of victory.

34:33.340 --> 34:39.186
And just as God had promised those walls came tumbling down and the Israelites went in and took the city.

34:39.330 --> 34:44.499
and they received the promise that God had made to them.

34:44.519 --> 34:50.749
You know, here in a moment I'm actually gonna invite the worship team to come out and join me and we're gonna stand to our feet in just a moment, we're gonna worship.

34:51.931 --> 34:56.018
And you know what, we don't worship because God

34:56.354 --> 34:57.638
needs to hear how great He is.

34:57.698 --> 34:58.520
God knows who He is.

34:58.841 --> 35:00.506
God knows how great He is.

35:00.586 --> 35:03.715
The Word tells us that everything in creation brings glory to God.

35:03.735 --> 35:06.082
The sun, when it rises, brings Him glory.

35:06.102 --> 35:08.268
The sun, when it sets, brings Him glory.

35:08.308 --> 35:11.858
The waves, that turn bring glory to Him.

35:12.738 --> 35:15.262
We don't worship and praise because God needs it.

35:15.562 --> 35:19.168
We worship and praise because the devil needs to hear our praise.

35:19.388 --> 35:24.796
Because can I tell you, there's something that happens when the devil hears you claim your victory.

35:24.816 --> 35:28.783
There's something that happens when you lift up your battle cry.

35:29.003 --> 35:33.410
That is specific to your season, your situation, your pain.

35:34.351 --> 35:38.898
And so here in just a moment, we're gonna worship and we're gonna sing out together when we do.

35:40.706 --> 35:43.330
I want to think about the battle cry that you're lifting up.

35:45.313 --> 35:50.100
That passion that has been dead on the inside of you.

35:53.465 --> 35:55.669
I believe God wants to stir it up in this moment.

35:58.473 --> 36:03.160
Those dreams that you've put to rest because you're tired of being disappointed.

36:03.500 --> 36:05.443
God wants to stir them back up again.

36:05.503 --> 36:09.970
That marriage that you have given up on

36:11.586 --> 36:12.548
You're just roommates.

36:12.568 --> 36:13.630
You're just living together.

36:13.670 --> 36:14.933
You're just doing life.

36:14.993 --> 36:16.577
You're just staying together for the kids.

36:16.897 --> 36:19.763
God wants to stir up that passion once again.

36:19.824 --> 36:25.516
So with every head, bow, and every eye closed, I'm going to pray for us.

36:25.536 --> 36:27.320
And if that's you today and you say, you know what?

36:28.362 --> 36:32.210
I want to lift up my battle cry and it's going to be a battle cry of victory.

36:33.442 --> 36:51.506
that passion that is laid dormant in your heart in this moment listen I believe that when we stand to our feet and you release that passion that is laid dormant in your heart and you begin to stir up your faith and you begin to stir up those dreams as we sing out God you are good

36:52.130 --> 36:58.177
I know my situation may not look good, but God, I know that you are good.

36:58.217 --> 37:00.920
God, I know my marriage doesn't look good.

37:01.220 --> 37:04.664
It's falling apart, but God, I believe that you are good.

37:04.884 --> 37:10.670
God, I know my ministry does not look good, but God, I believe you are good.

37:10.791 --> 37:15.676
Father, we come to you in this moment.

37:15.696 --> 37:21.202
Father, I pray for every heart and every soul.

37:21.346 --> 37:22.988
Those who have put their passion aside.

37:23.008 --> 37:26.774
Those who have laid their dreams to rest, God.

37:28.036 --> 37:48.466
I pray right now in this moment that you will begin to stir something up on the inside of us, God, so that when we stand to our feet, God, that we jump up in expectation, ready to worship, ready to praise, believing that you have won the war, God, the enemy may have won some battles, but you have won the war.

37:50.850 --> 37:53.178
So right now, we commit this moment to you, God.

37:53.680 --> 37:54.442
We thank you.

37:54.763 --> 37:56.128
We bless you, Father.

37:56.349 --> 38:00.242
We believe that you are our peace, God, where there is no peace, God.

38:00.463 --> 38:02.610
We believe that you are our strength.

38:02.658 --> 38:26.196
to give us that energy that we need to keep moving from battle to battle to battle to battle we believe that you are love we believe that you are our joy we believe that you are our defender we believe that you are our justice and it's in Jesus name that we pray come on stand up to your feet lift your hands

